# Nebutra-Sailor — Cursor Rules

## Project Overview

**Nebutra-Sailor** is an enterprise-grade SaaS monorepo for AI-native, multi-tenant platforms.

- **Runtime**: Node.js 22+, pnpm 10.32+
- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router, React 19, Turbopack)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 + CSS variables from `@nebutra/tokens`
- **Language**: TypeScript 5.9 (strict mode)
- **Linter**: Biome (NOT ESLint)
- **Testing**: Vitest (unit) + Playwright (E2E)
- **License**: AGPL-3.0

## Repository Structure

```
apps/
  landing-page/   Next.js 16 — marketing site (next-intl, 7 locales)
  web/            Next.js 16 — authenticated SaaS dashboard (Clerk auth)
  api-gateway/    Hono + OpenAPI — backend APIs (Zod, middleware stack)
  storybook/      Storybook 8.x — component documentation
  design-docs/    Next.js 16 + Fumadocs — internal docs
  studio/         Sanity Studio v5 — CMS
  docs/           Mintlify — public product docs

packages/
  ui/             PRIMARY component library — Radix + HeroUI + Lobe UI
  tokens/         Runtime CSS variables — SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH for theming
  brand/          Brand primitives (colors, gradients, motion)
  theme/          Multi-theme CSS (6 oklch presets)
  icons/          541 Geist icons as tree-shakable TSX
  db/             Prisma v7 + PostgreSQL
  billing/        Stripe integration
  identity/       Auth abstraction (Clerk adapter)
  email/          Resend transactional email
  ai-sdk/         Vercel AI SDK wrapper
  permissions/    RBAC/ABAC — CASL + OpenFGA
  webhooks/       Outbound webhooks — Svix
  metering/       Usage metering — ClickHouse
  logger/         Structured logging (Sentry)
  errors/         Typed error definitions
  audit/          Audit log (37 action types)
```

## CRITICAL Import Rules

```tsx
// ✅ UI components
import { Button, Input, Card } from "@nebutra/ui/components";

// ✅ Layout wrappers
import { PageHeader, EmptyState, LoadingState, ErrorState } from "@nebutra/ui/layout";

// ✅ Icons — Geist preferred, Lucide for generic
import { Search, Settings } from "@nebutra/icons";
import { ChevronRight } from "lucide-react";

// ✅ Theme
import { ThemeProvider, useTheme } from "@nebutra/tokens";

// ✅ Utilities
import { cn } from "@nebutra/ui/utils";

// ❌ NEVER import from @primer/react (removed)
// ❌ NEVER add new HeroUI imports unless Radix has NO equivalent
// ❌ NEVER import JS color tokens from @nebutra/ui/theme
```

## Styling Rules

```tsx
// ✅ Semantic CSS variables (Tailwind token classes)
<div className="bg-neutral-1 text-neutral-12 border-neutral-7" />

// ✅ Brand colors
<div className="bg-blue-9 text-cyan-11" />

// ✅ Brand gradient
<h1 style={{ background: "var(--brand-gradient)", WebkitBackgroundClip: "text", WebkitTextFillColor: "transparent" }} />

// ✅ Status colors
<div className="text-[color:var(--status-warning)]" />

// ❌ NEVER hardcode hex values
<div style={{ color: "#0033FE" }} />  // → use var(--brand-primary)
<div className="bg-[#f8fafc]" />     // → use bg-neutral-2

// Container widths
// text content: max-w-4xl
// feature sections: max-w-[1400px]
// NEVER: max-w-5xl, max-w-7xl
```

## Animation Rules

```tsx
// ✅ Always use AnimateIn for entrance animations
import { AnimateIn, AnimateInGroup } from "@nebutra/ui/components";

<AnimateIn preset="emerge"><YourComponent /></AnimateIn>
<AnimateIn preset="emerge" inView><Section /></AnimateIn>

// Staggered list
<AnimateInGroup stagger="normal">
  {items.map(item => <AnimateIn key={item.id} preset="fadeUp"><Card /></AnimateIn>)}
</AnimateInGroup>

// Presets: emerge, flow, fade, fadeUp, scale
// ❌ NEVER: raw motion.div with hardcoded initial/animate values
```

## Component Variants

```tsx
// ✅ Use CVA for all component variants
import { cva, type VariantProps } from "class-variance-authority";
import { cn } from "@nebutra/ui/utils";

const variants = cva("base", {
  variants: { size: { sm: "p-4", md: "p-6", lg: "p-8" } },
  defaultVariants: { size: "md" },
});
```

## Next.js 16 Rules

- Default to **Server Components** — only add `'use client'` for interactivity
- Use `proxy.ts` NOT `middleware.ts` (renamed in Next.js 16)
- All request APIs are async: `await cookies()`, `await headers()`, `await params`
- Use `Cache Components` (`'use cache'`) instead of PPR
- Use Server Actions (`'use server'`) for mutations
- Data fetching on client: use TanStack Query + typed API client

## API Gateway (Hono)

```ts
// Route files in: apps/api-gateway/src/routes/
// Middleware stack: trace → CORS → compression → security → rate-limit →
//                  idempotency → metering → audit → versioning → tenant

// Permissions middleware
import { requirePermission } from "@nebutra/permissions";
app.post("/api/v1/resource", requirePermission("create", "Resource"), handler);

// Tenant context
import { getCurrentTenant } from "@nebutra/tenant";
const tenant = getCurrentTenant(); // { tenantId, plan, ... }
```

## Authentication

```ts
// apps/web/src/lib/auth.ts helpers
import { getAuth, requireAuth, requireOrg, getTenantContext } from "@/lib/auth";

// Server Component
const { userId, orgId } = await getAuth();

// Protected page — redirects to /sign-in if not authed
await requireAuth();

// Org check — redirects to /select-org if no org
await requireOrg();
```

## Testing Requirements

- Minimum **80% coverage** (lines/functions), 70% branches
- Unit tests with Vitest: `packages/*/src/**/*.test.ts`
- E2E with Playwright: `e2e/*.spec.ts`
- Architecture tests: `pnpm test:arch`
- Every new component **MUST** have a Storybook story

## What NEVER to Do

```tsx
// ❌ NEVER: @primer/react
// ❌ NEVER: console.log in production (use @nebutra/logger)
// ❌ NEVER: hardcoded secrets (use env vars)
// ❌ NEVER: hardcoded hex brand colors (use CSS vars)
// ❌ NEVER: raw motion.div with hardcoded values
// ❌ NEVER: new component without Storybook story
// ❌ NEVER: mutations via Route Handlers (use Server Actions)
// ❌ NEVER: middleware.ts (use proxy.ts in Next.js 16)
```

